For Python clients (Boto3): You can configure the client when creating the session.
python
import boto3
s3_client = boto3.client(
    's3',
    endpoint_url='http://localhost:9878', // Replace with your Ozone S3 Gateway URL
    aws_access_key_id='YOUR_ACCESS_KEY',
    aws_secret_access_key='YOUR_SECRET_KEY',
    config=boto3.session.Config(signature_version='s3v4', s3={'addressing_style': 'path'})
)
For AWS CLI: You can set the addressing style in your AWS CLI configuration.
bash
aws configure set s3.addressing_style path
Then use the --endpoint-url flag in your commands. 
2. Configure Ozone S3 Gateway for Virtual-Hosted Style (Alternative) 
If you prefer to use the virtual-hosted style on the client side, you can enable it on the Ozone S3 Gateway by setting a domain name in the ozone-site.xml file: 
xml
<property>
  <name>ozone.s3g.domain.name</name>
  <value>s3g.internal</value>
</property>
After this configuration, you would access your buckets using http://bucketname.s3g.internal:port. 
